  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Community Engagement, Information Sharing and Capacity Building in COVID-19 Response in North-East Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to strengthening community engagement, information sharing and capacity building in COVID-19 response in north-east Nigeria. To address widespread rumours and misbelief surrounding the COVID-19 pandemic and aid delivered by humanitarian organisations, the project aims to reach a total of 50,000 vulnerable people throughout Borno, Adamawa and Yobe (BAY) states with effective behavioural change communication and build the capacity of 100 aid workers in adopting key Inter-Agency Standing Committee guidance for programming amidst COVID-19 including awareness raising and sensitization on disease prevention measures, in line with the Nigeria Humanitarian Fund Allocation Strategy, both in terms of activities, target locations and beneficiary types.</narrative>
  </description>
